{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} {{Use Australian English|date=August 2016}} The '''United Christian Party''' was a minor [[Australia]]n political party active between 1972 and 1974, and again in 1980. Following 1980 it was renamed the '''Australian Christian Party''' and contested the [[Australian federal election, 1983|1983 election]] as such.
Originally formed in [[South Australia]], its platform listed the election of a non-party-bound [[Christian]] to the [[Australian Senate|Senate]], the development of the [[Australian Aboriginal|Aboriginal]] race with the rest of the community, [[monarchism]] and the preservation of the [[Australian flag]]'s current form as its aims. It contested the Senate in 1974 and the [[Australian House of Representatives|House of Representatives]] (in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]]n seats) in 1980 and 1983.<ref>{{Cite book | last = Jaensch | first = Dean | authorlink = |author2=Mathieson, David | title = A plague on both your houses: minor parties in Australia | publisher = [[Allen and Unwin]] | date = 1998 | location = | pages = 64, 68 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=NMrav_dyyY0C&pg=PA58&lpg=PA58&dq=%22Engineered+Australia+Plan+Party%22&source=bl&ots=mth28vQNFD&sig=yctRYbykiyok9WMPK2MRjsQT1Os&hl=en&ei=UgRpS7jNI5aekQW-obW2DQ&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CAkQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=%22Engineered%20Australia%20Plan%20Party%22&f=false | doi = | id = | isbn = 1-86448-421-7}}</ref>
